      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's definitely a sign you need to stop whatever you're doing immediately. Those symptoms are classic signs of heat exhaustion, which is more serious than simple dehydration. You need to find a cool, shaded spot, and then start sipping on electrolyte drinks—plain water won't cut it. If you feel worse, try a quick head-to-toe cooling soak while you take a few minutes to catch your breath.",
